LUSAKA &#8211; Zambia&#8217;s inflation slowed to 6.7 percent year-on-year in March from 6.8 percent in February, the statistics office said on Thursday.The monthly inflation slowed to 0.3 percent from 1.0 percent in the previous month, the Central Statistics Office said.&#8220;The decline in the year on year inflation rate is mainly attributed to price changes in food items,&#8221; the statistics agency said in a statement.